            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "Thanks for the extra diagnostics.  This doesn't look to me like the behaviour has changed recently.\n\nIt's slightly hard to know what the best thing to do in all cases is.\n\nIf you're building in an isolated environment then both absolute and relative paths are kind of useless (they'll be gone by the time you actually try to access them) but relative paths are at least reproducible.\n\nIf you're using system packages then absolute paths are useful if you're running locally (or running somewhere with the same layout) and should at least be reproducible. They aren't useful if you're building packages that are installed elsewhere.",
