            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "> It's slightly hard to know what the best thing to do in all cases is.\n\nI think the intent behind the code (as stated in the [comment](https://github.com/cython/cython/blob/master/Cython/Compiler/Scanning.py#L198)) is correct i.e. leave the path absolute if it is outside the current directory but the implementation is wrong because it is depending on an error being raised which is never raised by the called function i.e. `os.path.relpath`.",
